<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="875" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/846: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jones</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-27T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            27, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your August 19, 6 P.M.</p>
                            <p>Department cannot recognize Government of Quiros in Costa Rica, it
                                being a creature of Tinoco. Government must be formed in accord with
                                old constitution and free election must occur.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>